
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeStyle rectangle

class Customer {
  +String name
  +String contactInfo
  +List<Car> registeredCars
}

class Car {
  +String licensePlate
  +String make
  +String model
  +String year
  +boolean isSelfDriving
  +Customer owner
  +List<Ride> rides
  +List<Accident> accidents
}

class Ride {
  +Date date
  +Location pickupLocation
  +Location dropoffLocation
  +Time pickupTime
  +Time dropoffTime
  +Duration duration
  +Distance distance
  +int numberOfPassengers
  +double fee
  +String typeOfRequest
  +Customer leadCustomer
  +List<Customer> sharedCustomers
  +Car car
}

class Accident {
  +Date date
  +Location location
  +double damageAmount
  +Car car
}

class Location {
  +String address
  +double latitude
  +double longitude
}

class RideHail extends Ride {
  +int maxPassengers (6)
}

class RideShare extends Ride {
  +int maxPassengers (10)
  +double negotiatedFee
}

' Relationships
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Car : owns
Car "1" -- "1..*" Ride : has
Ride "1" -- "1" Customer : leadCustomer
Ride "1" -- "0..*" Customer : sharedCustomers
Car "1" -- "0..*" Accident : has
RideHail "--|> Ride"
RideShare "--|> Ride"

@enduml

---

### ✅ Summary of Classes and Relationships:

- **Customer**: Represents users who can either be drivers or passengers. They may own cars and have ride history.
- **Car**: Represents both self-driving and user-owned vehicles. Each car belongs to a customer and may have ride and accident records.
- **Ride**: Abstract class representing all types of rides (ride-hail and ride-share). Contains common attributes like time, location, etc.
- **RideHail**: Subclass of `Ride` for on-demand hailing services with specific constraints.
- **RideShare**: Subclass of `Ride` for carpooling services with flexible pricing and more passengers allowed.
- **Accident**: Stores information about incidents involving a car.
- **Location**: A simple class to represent geographical coordinates and addresses.

